## Investigation (the answer)
Grepped weave/trace_server for digest computation. BOTH server impls compute
ALL digests via the same weave.shared.digest functions the corpus pins:
- sqlite_trace_server.obj_create:1897 / clickhouse:1917,2030 ->
  compute_object_digest_result(req.obj.val, req.obj.builtin_object_class)
- table_create -> compute_row_digest + compute_table_digest (sqlite:2369/2442,
  clickhouse:2487/2542)
- file_create -> compute_file_digest (sqlite:2813, clickhouse:5936)
- object_creation_utils.py:8 imports compute_file_digest/compute_object_digest.
So there is ONE canonicalization implementation by design (digest.py docstring:
"centralizes digest calculation logic to ensure consistency between the client
and server"). The PR7 library test therefore already verifies the exact code the
server runs -- but it calls the functions directly, not through the write path.
Gap: nothing asserted that a real obj_create/table_create/file_create returns the
corpus digest, i.e. corpus == server was implied by a code-read, not asserted.

